Description: The Flight into Egypt: a night piece; the Virgin seated on a donkey holding the Christ Child, while St Joseph leads the way towards the left while holding a lantern; sixth state with cross hatching over nose of donkey, Joseph's right hand, sleeve and chest, vertical lines added to lower part of light panels in lantern, before posthumous reworking of the plate; Jean de Bary impression, falsification with surface tone. 1651 Etching, burin and drypoint, printed with heavy surface tone, wiped around faces Watermark: Arms of Amsterdam (Hinterding catalogue, variant D.c. or D.f.)
Curator's comments: For comment and an impression of first state see also F,4.103.
